óŸdarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/lang-guide/chapters/types/basic_types/glob.mdŸ@b45bf8962a0a1ec2bfe972e810693b8c20b1ed5b1561e0b3baf258293c89c8ff§Globë® command⁄Z``glob``
The 
[link: /commands/docs/glob.md] ``glob``
 
command
 provides additional globbing options. It is distinct from the 
``glob``
 
type
.
Simple example:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
glob *.nu
# => [ /home/you/dev/foo.nu /home/you/dev/bar.nu ]

```
Notice the glob, after expansion, always returns a 
``list``
 of fully qualified pathnames.
